==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eozoic
<hw>E`o*zo"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Eozo⟦oum⟧n</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to
rocks or strata older than the Paleozoic, in many of which the
eozo⟦oum⟧n has been found.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This term has been proposed for the strata formerly
called <xex>Azoic</xex>, and is preferred especially by those geologists
who regard the eozo⟦oum⟧n as of organic origin. See
<er>Arch⟦ae⟧an</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eozoon</ent>⟦br⟧
